# LocalPlus 🏪

> The all-in-one survival kit for small shops — manage smarter, sell more, compete harder.

## Project Structure

```
localplus/
├── backend/
│   ├── main.py                    ← FastAPI app entry point
│   ├── database.py                ← SQLAlchemy ORM models + DB init
│   ├── auth.py                    ← JWT auth helpers
│   ├── requirements.txt
│   ├── .env.example
│   ├── models/
│   │   └── schemas.py             ← Pydantic request/response schemas
│   ├── routes/
│   │   ├── auth.py                ← POST /auth/register, /auth/login
│   │   ├── products.py            ← CRUD /products
│   │   ├── sales.py               ← POST /sales, GET /sales/summary
│   │   ├── forecast.py            ← POST /forecast (AI Demand Oracle)
│   │   └── udhaar.py              ← CRUD /udhaar (credit ledger)
│   └── services/
│       └── demand_oracle.py       ← Prophet + XGBoost forecasting engine
│
└── frontend/
    ├── index.html
    ├── vite.config.js
    ├── package.json
    └── src/
        ├── main.jsx               ← React entry point
        ├── App.jsx                ← Router + protected routes
        ├── index.css              ← Global design tokens + base styles
        ├── api/
        │   └── client.js          ← Axios instance + all API calls
        ├── components/
        │   └── Sidebar.jsx        ← Navigation sidebar
        └── pages/
            ├── Login.jsx          ← Login screen
            ├── Register.jsx       ← Register screen
            ├── Dashboard.jsx      ← Revenue chart + stat cards
            ├── Inventory.jsx      ← Product CRUD
            ├── SaleEntry.jsx      ← Cart-style sale recorder
            ├── Forecast.jsx       ← AI Demand Oracle UI
            └── Udhaar.jsx         ← Credit ledger
```

---

## Quick Start

### 1. Backend

```bash
cd backend

# Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate        # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Set up environment variables
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env and add your API keys

# Run the server
uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000
```

API docs available at: **http://localhost:8000/docs**

---

### 2. Frontend

```bash
cd frontend

npm install
npm run dev
```

App available at: **http://localhost:5173**

---

## Environment Variables (backend/.env)

| Variable | Description |
|---|---|
| `OPENWEATHER_API_KEY` | [OpenWeatherMap](https://openweathermap.org/api) free tier key |
| `SECRET_KEY` | Long random string for JWT signing |
| `TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID` | Twilio SID for WhatsApp reminders (optional) |
| `TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN` | Twilio auth token (optional) |

---

## API Endpoints

| Method | Path | Description |
|---|---|---|
| POST | `/auth/register` | Register new shop |
| POST | `/auth/login` | Login, get JWT |
| GET | `/products/` | List all products |
| POST | `/products/` | Add product |
| PUT | `/products/{id}` | Update product |
| DELETE | `/products/{id}` | Delete product |
| POST | `/sales/` | Record a sale |
| GET | `/sales/summary` | 7-day revenue summary |
| GET | `/sales/history/{id}` | Daily qty sold (for Oracle) |
| POST | `/forecast/` | Run AI Demand Oracle |
| GET | `/udhaar/` | List pending credit |
| POST | `/udhaar/` | Add credit entry |
| PATCH | `/udhaar/{id}/paid` | Mark as paid |

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Frontend | React 18, Vite, React Router, Recharts, Axios |
| Backend | FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, Pydantic v2, Uvicorn |
| Database | SQLite (dev) → PostgreSQL (production) |
| Auth | JWT via python-jose + bcrypt |
| AI Model | Prophet + XGBoost (demand forecasting) |
| Weather | OpenWeatherMap API |
| Notifications | Twilio WhatsApp + Fast2SMS |

---

## Upgrading to Production

1. **Database**: swap `sqlite:///./localplus.db` in `database.py` for a `postgresql://` URL
2. **SECRET_KEY**: use a cryptographically random 64-char string
3. **CORS**: restrict `allow_origins` to your actual domain
4. **ML libs**: uncomment the full Prophet + XGBoost block in `demand_oracle.py`
5. **Deploy backend**: Railway / Render / EC2 with `uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0`
6. **Deploy frontend**: Vercel / Netlify (`npm run build` → `dist/` folder)